preds: ['', 'The hotel features a nice inside courtyard with atrium and there is art work throughout.', 'The hotel has nightly activities, like a "mixology" presentation at the bar. There\'s nightly stargazing on one of the lawns with a telescope and professional guide. On Saturday night they also had a "dive in movie" in the spa pool (it was "Frozen").', '', 'The hotel has an outdoor spring/summer space.', '', '', 'The hotel offered coloring books and crayons to occupy our kids.', 'The hotel is on St. Pete Beach. They have a dock across the street at their sister property on the I tercoadtal (and they even loan fishing gear). They have a little beach bar hut and Chik File A room food service. They have a delivery set up with Chik Fil A from across the street.', 'The hotel is kid friendly with scavenger hunts, ranger wildlife lessons, and free chocolate. They have a tortoise.', 'The hotel has photos in the hallway of the original orphanage.', '', 'The hotel has a sheep and 3 goats.', '', '']

preds: ['', 'The hotel has a rooftop pool. They have a fitness room.', 'The hotel has nightly activities, like a "mixology" presentation at the bar. They have a delivery set up with Chik Fil A from across the street.', 'The hotel is kid friendly with scavenger hunts, ranger wildlife lessons, and free chocolate. They have a tortoise.', 'The hotel has photos in the hallway of the original orphanage.', 'The hotel has an area out where you can play corn-hole, ping pong, rent jets and more. They have a little area were if fishing is your thing, bring your rods and do so.', 'The hotel has a sheep and 3 goats.', '', '']

preds: ['The hotel is a gem in the heart of Philadelphia. It\'s a cozy, quaint, and charming property. The decor is chic and attractive: big wooden desk, hardwood floors, couches and throw pillows: Looks more like a friend\'s apartment than a hotel. Free breakfast is always a plus for those of us with limited time. It\'s not a hot breakfast (I\'ve had so many mass-produced bad ones, so trust me on that) but greek yogurt, a huge croissant, an orange and some cranberry juice hits the spot! They leave it at your door though, instead of ringing your bell to wake you up. So if you ask for it to be delivered at 7 a.m., check outside your door; by 7:01 it WILL be there. Coffee, a variety of teas, cold and hot water, as well as ice and a bowl of assorted fruit are available 24/7 in the lobby. There are doorbells for each room, and the hotel can only be accessed after hours if you have a key card. There are doorbells for each room, and the hotel can only be accessed after hours if you have a key card. The staff is very polite: one of the few places in Philly where someone will actually say "good morning" to you (No, seriously. I lived there for 5 years, so trust me on that). They\'re also extremely helpful. When I checked in the night before, the gentleman at the reservation desk called to make sure I had a cab waiting for me at 8:15 the next morning so that I could make my speaking engagement on time. While I\'ve read a few reviews talking about the noise level of this place. My room was closest to the reception desk and I never heard a peep. There were people out and about, but I didn\'t hear a thing.
